G-BX-OBEY-AB — SP_BYTEEXACT=1 obedience A/B on the served path (2026-07-02)
============================================================================
PRE-REGISTERED QUESTION (G-L5-OBEY-REPRO next-step #1): serve the full exact-integer forward
(SP_BYTEEXACT=1) and re-run the 61-para harness. If obedience stabilizes/changes, the fragility
is the float forward and byte-exact is the fix surface.

SETUP: receipt-exact serve (_faithful_serve_l5.bat) with SP_BYTEEXACT=1 exported to the daemon
process; same harness (tests/perf/_g_faithful_recall.py, USE_PARA=1, seam=l5bx); same 61-episode
registry; build = engine ad27b1b.

RESULT: **61/61 answers BYTE-IDENTICAL to the plain (no SP_BYTEEXACT) serve** (seam=l5v2 vs
l5bx json rows). Tally identical: OBEY 25 / LEAK 30 / BOTH 1 / OTHER 5 (40.98%). Latency
unchanged (~10s/turn). SP_BYTEEXACT=1 is a NO-OP on the served kv-decode path.

WHY (code-grounded):
- The served chat ALREADY runs byte-exact per request: routes.rs defaults `byteexact=true`
  (routes.rs:415) -> kv::set_byteexact -> `gemma4_kv_byteexact_set` (cuda_forward.cu:~4445)
  sets the device `d_bx_flag` AND `s->bx_on` -> exact-integer nonlinear islands
  (RMSNorm/RoPE/GELU) + exact decode attention (k_attn_decode_win_bx / ring_bx).
- SP_BYTEEXACT (env) feeds the same d_bx_flag on the one-shot decode entry — redundant when
  the per-request flag is already on. Hence bit-identical output.
- The REMAINING FLOAT SURFACE on the served path = the cuBLAS float GEMMs in PREFILL (and any
  non-dp4a GEMM feeding KV/logits). G-BYTEEXACT-FORWARD-12B proved the ONE-SHOT forward exact
  end-to-end; that envelope was never extended to the served kv PREFILL.

INTERPRETATION (the honest chain):
1. Today's stack is STRONGLY deterministic: 4 independent serves (plain x3, BX x1) agree
   byte-for-byte on all 61 answers.
2. The 07-01 receipts (86.89% / 85.2%) diverge from ALL of today's runs despite pinned
   binaries (exact a14fee4 rebuild), model, CUDA lib, driver, corpus.
3. Byte-exact-as-currently-scoped is ruled out as the differing factor (this gate).
4. => The 07-01 divergence lived in the float-GEMM/prefill environment of that serve:
   leading suspects = cuBLAS algorithm/workspace selection under different VRAM pressure
   (other models/rails resident that day), or an engine env var exported in that session
   (SP_ENGINE_FP16 / SP_ENGINE_F16_ACT / capture rails) that alters float rounding.
   The receipt did not dump its environment — cannot be settled retroactively.

VERDICT: the pre-registered hypothesis is ANSWERED-NEGATIVE as scoped (SP_BYTEEXACT does not
change served obedience) and the THESIS IS SHARPENED: the byte-exact envelope has a COVERAGE
GAP on the served path — prefill GEMMs are float. Closing that gap (exact-integer / dp4a
prefill GEMMs on the kv path, the same OK_Q4B substrate the decode GEMV already uses) is the
fix surface that would make paraphrase-obedience receipts build/environment-stable.

LAW EXTENSIONS (banked):
- Every obey receipt: build SHA + same-day canary + **full SP_* env dump** in the log.
- "byte-exact ON" claims must name the ENVELOPE (islands+attention vs full forward vs prefill).

